{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"451ec4d2-fcef-488d-aeaf-be6945b02074","content":"In MSTest 3.x (which you're using), the recommended pattern is:\n\n1. **Constructor** — for sync setup + `TestContext` injection\n2. **`[TestInitialize]` async method** — for async setup\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Sync init: inject TestContext via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async init: use [TestInitialize]\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Initialized\");\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        var result = await _service.GetDataAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` replaces the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern (though the property still works).\n- The constructor runs first (sync setup), then `[TestInitialize]` runs (async setup) — once per test method.\n- For **one-time class-level** async setup, use `[ClassInitialize]` on a `static async Task` method.\n- For cleanup, use `[TestCleanup]` (per-test) or `[ClassCleanup]` (per-class), both support `async Task`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27414778-6996-4b7a-96b2-ba557b363a07","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is using MSTest 3.8.2 with .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), constructor injection for `TestContext` is supported. Let me provide guidance on how to set up both synchronous and asynchronous initialization.\n\nIn MSTest v3+:\n- You can inject `TestContext` via constructor\n- For synchronous init, use the constructor\n- For asynchronous init, implement `IAsyncInitialization` or use `[TestInitialize]` with an async method\n\nLet me provide a clear, concise answer.","outputTokens":524,"requestId":"E3D0:39929D:67F9C7:77B301:6A05289C"},"id":"aa786276-8cf2-4319-89f8-90cdcf95bbde","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:43:04.429Z","parentId":"23b58fef-c3ce-4e12-abd4-e228637d3f89"}
